The '''''João Coutinho''-class corvettes''' were a series of corvettes built for the [[Portuguese Navy]] for service in Portugal's African colonies. The corvettes were designed in Portugal by naval engineer Rogério de Oliveira, but the urgent need of their services in the [[Portuguese Colonial War]] meant that the construction of the ships was assigned to foreign shipyards. Six ships were built; the first three ships were built by [[Blohm + Voss]] and the remaining three by [[BAZAN|''Empresa Nacional Bazán'']]. The ships were launched in 1970 and 1971.<ref name=aniceto>{{cite book | last = Afonso | first = Aniceto |author2=Carlos de Matos Gomes | title = Guerra Colonial | publisher = Editorial Noticias | year = 2000 | pages = 378–380 | isbn = 972-46-1192-2 }} (Portuguese text)</ref><ref name=coutinho>{{cite web | title = Classe João Coutinho | url=http://www.marinha.pt/PT/amarinha/meiosoperacionais/superficie/classejoaocoutinho/Pages/ClasseJoaoCoutinho.aspx | accessdate = 2011-08-05}} (Portuguese text)</ref>
From 1970 until the end of the conflict in 1975, the corvettes were used for patrol and fire-support missions in [[Portuguese Angola|Angola]], [[Portuguese Mozambique|Mozambique]], [[Portuguese Guinea|Guinea]] and [[Colonial Cape Verde|Cape Verde]]. After the African colonies gained their independence, the corvettes were assigned to patrol duties in Portuguese territorial waters.<ref name=aniceto/><ref name=coutinho/>
The ''João Coutinho'' class served as the basis for several other designs: [[Baptista de Andrade-class corvette|''Baptista de Andrade''-class]] corvettes<ref>{{cite web | title = NRP Baptista de Andrade | url=http://www.marinha.pt/PT/amarinha/meiosoperacionais/superficie/baptistadeandrade/Pages/classebaptistaandrade.aspx | accessdate = 2011-08-05 }} (Portuguese text)</ref> (Portugal), [[Descubierta-class corvette|''Descubierta''-class]] corvettes<ref>{{cite book | last = Miller | first = David | title = The Illustrated Directory of Warships: From 1860 to the Present Day | publisher = Greenwich Editions | year = 2004 | pages = 248–249 | isbn = 0-86288-677-5}}</ref> ([[Spain]], [[Egypt]] and [[Morocco]]), [[Espora-class corvette|''Espora''-class]] ([[MEKO 140]]) corvettes<ref>{{cite web | title = Armada Argentina - Sitio Oficial - Reseña Histórica | url = http://www.ara.mil.ar/hist_sigloxx.asp | accessdate = 2009-02-13 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080206131124/http://www.ara.mil.ar/hist_sigloxx.asp |archivedate = 2008-02-06}} (Spanish text. Copy in Internet Archive cache)</ref> ([[Argentina]]) and [[D'Estienne d'Orves-class aviso|''D'Estienne d'Orves''-class]] (A-69) avisos<ref>[http://www.operacional.pt/«a-corveta-portuguesa-dos-anos-70» A Corveta Portuguesa dos anos 70, Operacional: 2009]</ref> ([[France]], Argentina and [[Turkey]]) .
The ships were finally decommissioned in 2015.
